comment_data.body:
I might be misinterpreting your argument, but it seems to me like closing this requires fixing "this *and* that", rather that "this *instead* of that".

To recap the various discussions that happened here, in #34199 and #34272, my understanding of the current plan to fix the handling of empty buffers â€” no matter their editing history or the values of `(fix)eol` â€” is to:

1. make `nvim_buf_line_count(0)` return 0 (currently returns 1);
2. make `nvim_buf_get_offset(0, 1)` error due to oob index (currently returns 1);
3. make `nvim_buf_get_lines(0, 0, 1, true)` error due to oob index (currently returns `{ "" }`);
4. make `byte2line(1)` return -1 (currently returns 1 if buffer has been edited);
5. make `line2byte(1)` return -1 (currently returns 1 if buffer has been edited);
6. make sure `write` writes 0 bytes (currently writes `\n` if buffer has been edited and `eol` is on);


Also note that AFAICT nothing here is specific to `u`ndoing edits, as all the before-vs-after-like bugs can be reproduced by simply inserting and deleting text with `<BS>`.
